_evidence.text: additively manufactured using a mixture of pure Ti, Hf, Nb, and V powders
oxidized in an open-air tube furnace
yield strength of the as-fabricated T42 alloy decreased to ~681 MPa
a decrease in the yield strength to ~661 MPa
a slight decrease (approximately 25 MPa) in the yield strength
a significant decrease in the fracture strain (~7.5 %)
Yield strength as a function of tested temperatures
lattice constant of the T42 alloy was determined to be 3.3176 Å
yield strengths ranging from 680 to 635 MPa
electron beam selective melting at high temperature
selective laser melting, followed by annealing

Process_Info.Process_Text_For_AI: scanning speed 5 mm/s, hatching space 381 μm, working laser power 550 W, remelting power 800 W, layer thickness 200 μm, argon atmosphere <200 ppm O2 open-air tube furnace, durations 1h–120h remelting procedure applied
